name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
Visit the hill park during weekday evening.

Take grab and alight at car park, very easy to spot the the hill.

Attach photo do show that is not many people around during weekday.

Top of the hill really windy, nice place to relax to chit chat with your close one.

Disappointed that there is no "bed of flower" during the visit, maybe not the season or something else.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
12 Jul 2022: Cool breeze, scenic elevated walkway to Alexandra Arch and not forgetting the amazing “birds orchestra”

08 Jun 2022: Turn left or turn right? One will bring you to the elevated walkway of Forest Walk and Hort Park and the other one will bring you to the iconic Henderson Waves and Mount Faber Park. Nice and quiet environment...take a moment to listen to the birds singing or watch the squirrels in their natural surroundings.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
This could perhaps be one of the most underrated park.  It sits below Henderson Waves forming part of the Southern Ridges.
Found the short trail to be wonderfully green.  It even has a small little stream running thru it.  The trail looks very much abandoned & there lies the beauty of it
Oftentimes, everyone is on top of Henderson Waves & don't realized that beneath it, is another wonderful trail to be explored too.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text: Lack of services, such as restrooms, park benches, architectural lights for the pedestrians. However, the park is wonderful to take a rest and spend some cozy time with family and friends.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
A nice little hilltop to visit, which most might miss, if you’re walking from the Forest Trail to the Henderson Wave or vice versa.
Also the backdrop of many local acting scenes.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text: It’s a trail for jogging, hiking and walking.. Resting benches are at several points. Its soo and quite covered with green. Nice sceneries are all over the park. The Henderson gives a wide top scenery view which is so wonderful. Even though its sunny in the afternoon you won’t feel the heat since its soo windy..

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text: Telok Blangah Hill is serene and beautiful. Near this place there is an area with many beautiful huge black and white houses. Most of these bungalow houses are equipped with a nice and right size pool, huge garden and living space.  It is perfect for a morning walk but not late evening walk as some of the roads does not even have street lamp. This is a tranquil living, spacious, in the south of Singapore.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text: Cool walking day today, amidst the shady trees and on the way to Vivo City from Kent Ridge MRT. Just enough slopes up and down to enjoy a long 3 hour walk, without breaking much of a sweat 😂 Will definitely love to revisit, next time perhaps starting earlier before the sun rises 🌆and reaching Mt Faber before 11am heat☀️

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text: A wonderful tourist attracted limited only by the land size. The management have packed as many exhibits into this small park yet have made it so enriching. It is great timing that they are planning to move away since the neighbouring buildings are fast approaching the park perimeters due to industrial expansion.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text: It’s got lot of stairs making it easy to traverse. I’ve used it as a thoroughfare for southern ridges trail mostly towards VivoCity. name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
This park is the fastest route to the Henderson Waves if you are driving. There is a carpark halfway up and you can slowly trudge up the walkway to reach the Western end of the bridge.
Caution. It is a very steep climb.

On the other end there is a flower terrace that is quite hidden. It is  a great photo spot as shown in the attached pictures.

There is also a treetop walk that you can explore and it goes all the way to Alexandra Road.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
Telok Blangah Hill is situated at Telok Blangah Green, off Henderson Road, in Bukit Merah.

The current dividing line between Mount Faber and TBH seem to be Henderson Road. However, in the old days, these two hills and its many subsidiary summits seem to be known as being part of a long single hill ridge.

Before 1845, the long ridge that includes today's Mount Faber and TBH was simply called "Tulloh Blangan Hills" after the area along the southern coast of Singapore

We finished by the cable car and continued out to Sentosa.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text: This is pure gem by all means. This is part of south ridges (Mount Faber, Hort Park and Telok Blangah hill Park). This is best of the 3. This park has ample car parking at multiple places. The highlight is the Henderson wave bridge that connects this park with Hort Park. That itself require a separate view. From Car Park 1, a very short hike, you will be at the marvelous Henderson bridge. This has spectacular views which I suspect cant be seen from anywhere else. The otherside, has the terrace garden with beautiful views. All in all, this place is a complete different experience for those living in Singapore. This place will make us forget that we are in the citystate.

review_text:
Did a solo 2-hour hike to The Southern Ridges Trail. One of the famous trails in Singapore that showcases the calmness and beauty of Singapore's nature away from the City. Saw lots of squirrels and monkeys during the travel. The architecture of the bridges and walkway are topnotch. I highly recommend this activity when you go to Singapore.

MRT Kent Ridge..Science Park..Kent Ridge Park..Canopy Walk..Edible Garden..Floral Walk..Forest Walk..Hort Park..Southern Ridges..Telok Blangah Park..Henderson Waves..Mount Faber Park..Faber Peak.

Best DIY hike in SG.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text: It’s got lot of stairs making it easy to traverse. I’ve used it as a thoroughfare for southern ridges trail mostly towards VivoCity. It leads to Henderson waves, but is a beautiful park for walk, exercise and views of the forest. There are canopy walkways with ton of rich biodiversity including easily visible Bougainville and many species of birds. There’s also monkeys around, so be aware!!

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Singapore has a lot of greenery, a lot of natural parks, a lot of places for walking. Telok Blangah Hill Park is very suitable for hiking after a busy day. Tall trees create a natural sunshade, and there are vending machines along the route. Just walk and breathe the air. It is also very important that several parks are interconnected and form a whole natural complex.

(Original)
В Сингапуре много зелени,много природных парков,много мест для прогулок. Telok Blangah Hill Park очень подходит для пеших прогулок после напряжённых будней. Высокие деревья создают естественный зонтик от солнца,на маршруте есть аппараты для продажи напитков. Просто ходи и дыши воздухом. Ещё очень важно,что несколько парков соединены между собой и образуют целый природный комплекс.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) This park has fresh air and abundant plants. It is worth visiting frequently. It is a hike to relax your body and mind. It allows everyone to exercise and see beautiful scenery. Why not?

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Telok Blangah Hill park has a scenic sky bridge of about 5 kilometers. It is a good way to pass through close to the natural environment but reduce the damage. The bridge can also overlook the city and the coast. The scenery is very beautiful in the evening, it is worth visiting!

(Original)
Telok Blangah Hill park 有著約五公里的景觀空橋，能穿越親近自然環境但將破壞降低，是一個好的方法，橋上也可遠眺市區及海岸，傍晚來景色十分美麗，值得來！

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Love it. Great for walking, exercising. There are a lot of parking spaces, and the scenery on foot to Mount Faber Park is beautiful. You can pass a sky bridge linking two mountains at an altitude of 60 meters, which is very spectacular.

(Original)
喜欢这里 很适合步行，锻炼。停车位不少，步行到Mount Faber Park景色很美。可以路过一个海拔60米的链接两座山的天桥，很壮观。

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Very nice park on a small hill. Beautiful flower beds framing the original, not quite usual for Singapore, staircase leading to the top of the hill.
From the top there is a good view of the surroundings, the passenger harbor, Sentosa.
The best way to get there is by taxi, which will take you almost to the very top.
The toilet is located away from the top, in a small parking lot, this should be taken into account.
There are no cafes or other food outlets in the park.
In walking distance are Gillman barracks - a very interesting exhibition space.

(Original)
Очень приятный парк на небольшом холме. Прекрасные цветники, обрамляющие оригинальную, не совсем обычную для Сингапура, лестницу ведущую к вершине холма.
Сверху открывается неплохой вид на окрестности, пассажирскую гавань, Сентозу.
Добираться лучше на такси, которое довезет почти до самой вершины.
Туалет находится в стороне от вершины, на небольшой стоянке, это нужно иметь ввиду.
Кафе или иных точек питания в парке нет.
В пешей близости находятся Gillman barracks - очень интересное выставочное пространство.

But you can also run sports at the same time, because the place is indeed for people jogging, doing gymnastics together.

Tapi kalian juga bisa sekalian olahraga lari gitu2, karena tempatnya memang buat orang-orang jogging, senam bersama.

name: Telok Blangah Hill Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Great park in the middle of the city. We took the mrt to harborfront and then took the bus to hortPark. A bridge leads to Hill Park and Mount Faber Park. In the Hillpark you can walk over bridges and see the almost untouched nature from above. A great route for a two hour hike across green Singapore. Finally, you come out again at the mrt station harbourfront.

(Original)
Toller Park mitten in der Stadt. Wir sind mit der mrt bis harbourfront gefahren und dann weiter mit dem Bus zum hortPark. Über eine Brücke gelangt man in den Hillpark und den Mount faber Park. Im Hillpark läuft man über Brücken und kann die fast ünberührte Natur von oben betrachten. Eine tolle Strecke für eine zwei Stunden Wanderung quer durch das grüne Singapur. Zum Schluss kommt man wieder an der mrt Haltestelle harbourfront raus.
